 ;; Pass 3 — Decisions
 [:db/add -5 :decision/summary "Zones are the primary allocation unit — assign use types to zones, not cells."]
 [:db/add -5 :decision/rationale "Zones already encode terrain-awareness, buildability, road-splitting, and slope orientation. Cell-by-cell produces blobs or road chicken-and-egg problems."]
 [:db/add -5 :decision/affects -1]

 [:db/add -6 :decision/summary "Zone boundaries ARE the primary street network."]
 [:db/add -6 :decision/rationale "Solves the road-before-development problem: gaps between zones follow terrain and are natural street corridors."]
 [:db/add -6 :decision/affects -1]

 [:db/add -7 :decision/summary "Commercial doesn't work at zone level — it's fundamentally about road frontage."]
 [:db/add -7 :decision/rationale "Commercial claims frontage along roads one plot deep. The zone system creates the road network; commercial fills along it."]
 [:db/add -7 :decision/affects -1]

